            <thetext>IS:

qx.event.type.Touch.getRotation() does not work for IE10+, as this feature is only supported through MSGestures.

SHOULD:

The TouchCore handler is able to polyfill the calculation the of the rotation angle.

As IE does not allow to overwrite a event parameter, we should apply the polyfilled rotation value as &quot;_rotation&quot;.

The calculated value can be accessed through qx.event.type.Touch.getRotation()</thetext>
